    "Name": "Thunderbolt",
    "Details": "Introduced in 3091 at Trellshire Heavy Industries, this Thunderbolt returned to the successful design paradigm of missiles and lasers supported by heavy armor. A Heavy-Duty Gyro improved battlefield longevity. Thirteen tons of armor protect the 'Mech. An ER Large Laser, LRM-15, and SRM-2 are present, but the three medium lasers have been replaced by extended range versions. A pair of Small X-Pulse Lasers in the left arm provide anti-infantry capability. Two tons of LRM ammunition and a ton of SRM ammunition are stored in the left torso in a CASE II-protected bay.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Multi Trac</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.09</color></b>",
